HEADWORD: home-coming
<hw>home"-com`ing</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A return home.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kepeth this child, al be it foul or fayr,⟦br⟧
And eek my wyf, unto myn <qex>hoom-cominge</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A social event, usually held annually at colleges
and universities, to welcome visiting alumni; a type of school reunion
for graduates.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Home-driven</ent>⟦br⟧
